{
 "cells": [
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "08-md-intro",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# Network search: BFS + Dijkstra / A*\n",
    "\n",
    "**Algorithms:** `bfs_distances` and `shortest_path` from `zarr_vectors_tools.algorithms`\n",
    "\n",
    "Both run a standard frontier loop over a tools-side adjacency map built from the chunked store (intra-chunk edges resolved via the global-offset table, cross-chunk edges merged in from the cross array). Memory cost today: `O(N + E)`. Once core *Add 2* (per-chunk cross index) lands the implementation switches to true lazy expansion.\n",
    "\n",
    "1. Generate a weighted graph with realistic euclidean edge lengths\n",
    "2. Write the graph with `length` as an edge attribute\n",
    "3. `bfs_distances` from a seed — unweighted hop counts + predecessor reconstruction\n",
    "4. `shortest_path` with `weight=\"length\"` — Dijkstra\n",
    "5. `shortest_path` with a euclidean heuristic — A*; compare visited counts"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 1,
   "id": "08-imp",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Store: C:\\Users\\andre\\AppData\\Local\\Temp\\zvt_examples_fndmpv5p\\vessels.zarrvectors\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "import numpy as np, tempfile, os\n",
    "from zarr_vectors.lazy import open_zvr\n",
    "from zarr_vectors.types.graphs import write_graph, read_graph\n",
    "from zarr_vectors_tools.algorithms import bfs_distances, shortest_path\n",
    "\n",
    "_tmpdir = tempfile.mkdtemp(prefix=\"zvt_examples_\")\n",
    "STORE = os.path.join(_tmpdir, \"vessels.zarrvectors\")\n",
    "print(\"Store:\", STORE)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "08-md-1",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 1 · Generate a weighted graph\n",
    "\n",
    "Random points in a cube + a k-NN graph; edge weights are euclidean distances. Same shape as `04_graphs.ipynb` but spelled out here so the notebook stands alone."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 2,
   "id": "08-gen",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "nodes : 4,000\n",
      "edges : 12,157\n",
      "edge length [µm] : min=1.36  max=76.81  mean=34.20\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "from scipy.spatial import KDTree\n",
    "\n",
    "rng = np.random.default_rng(11)\n",
    "n_nodes = 4_000\n",
    "positions = rng.uniform(0, 600, (n_nodes, 3)).astype(np.float32)\n",
    "\n",
    "tree = KDTree(positions)\n",
    "_, nbrs = tree.query(positions, k=6)             # k=1 is self\n",
    "src = np.repeat(np.arange(n_nodes, dtype=np.int32), 5)\n",
    "dst = nbrs[:, 1:].flatten().astype(np.int32)\n",
    "\n",
    "mask  = src != dst\n",
    "edges = np.column_stack([src[mask], dst[mask]])\n",
    "edges = np.sort(edges, axis=1)\n",
    "edges = np.unique(edges, axis=0).astype(np.int32)\n",
    "\n",
    "edge_len = np.linalg.norm(\n",
    "    positions[edges[:, 0]] - positions[edges[:, 1]], axis=1\n",
    ").astype(np.float32)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"nodes : {n_nodes:,}\")\n",
    "print(f\"edges : {len(edges):,}\")\n",
    "print(f\"edge length [µm] : min={edge_len.min():.2f}  max={edge_len.max():.2f}  mean={edge_len.mean():.2f}\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "08-md-2",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 2 · Write the graph"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 3,
   "id": "08-write",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "vertex_count : 4,000\n",
      "chunk_shape  : (150.0, 150.0, 150.0)\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "write_graph(\n",
    "    STORE,\n",
    "    positions=positions,\n",
    "    edges=edges,\n",
    "    chunk_shape=(150., 150., 150.),\n",
    "    bin_shape=(37.5, 37.5, 37.5),\n",
    "    kind="graph",\n",
    "    link_attributes={\"length\": edge_len},\n",
    ")\n",
    "store = open_zvr(STORE)\n",
    "print(f\"vertex_count : {store[0].vertex_count:,}\")\n",
    "print(f\"chunk_shape  : {store.chunk_shape}\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "08-md-3",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 3 · `bfs_distances` from a seed\n",
    "\n",
    "Pick a corner node as the seed. The returned `distances` array uses `-1` for unreached nodes; `predecessors[v]` is the parent on the shortest path tree (`-1` for the source and for unreached nodes)."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 4,
   "id": "08-bfs",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "source = 27  pos=[ 8.7  6.1 53.1]\n",
      "target = 3962  pos=[559.8 579.6 557.6]\n",
      "\n",
      "reached nodes  : 4,000 / 4,000\n",
      "max hop count  : 31\n",
      "target hop count : 31\n",
      "BFS path length (hops) : 31\n",
      "BFS path euclidean len : 1255.92 µm\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# Seed = node closest to the origin corner; target = node closest to the\n",
    "# opposite corner. Reuse the index into the global vertex ordering that\n",
    "# read_graph returns (which is what the algorithms operate on).\n",
    "g = read_graph(STORE)\n",
    "P = g[\"positions\"]\n",
    "source = int(np.argmin(np.linalg.norm(P - np.array([  0,   0,   0]), axis=1)))\n",
    "target = int(np.argmin(np.linalg.norm(P - np.array([600, 600, 600]), axis=1)))\n",
    "print(f\"source = {source}  pos={P[source].round(1)}\")\n",
    "print(f\"target = {target}  pos={P[target].round(1)}\")\n",
    "\n",
    "bfs = bfs_distances(STORE, source=source)\n",
    "dist = bfs[\"distances\"]\n",
    "preds = bfs[\"predecessors\"]\n",
    "\n",
    "reached = int((dist >= 0).sum())\n",
    "print(f\"\\nreached nodes  : {reached:,} / {len(dist):,}\")\n",
    "print(f\"max hop count  : {int(dist.max())}\")\n",
    "print(f\"target hop count : {int(dist[target])}\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Reconstruct the hop path from predecessors.\n",
    "path_bfs = [target]\n",
    "while path_bfs[-1] != source:\n",
    "    path_bfs.append(int(preds[path_bfs[-1]]))\n",
    "path_bfs.reverse()\n",
    "print(f\"BFS path length (hops) : {len(path_bfs) - 1}\")\n",
    "print(f\"BFS path euclidean len : {np.linalg.norm(np.diff(P[path_bfs], axis=0), axis=1).sum():.2f} µm\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "08-md-4",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 4 · Dijkstra with edge weights\n",
    "\n",
    "Same `(source, target)` pair, but now the cost of each edge is its `length` attribute. The result is the geometrically shortest path, which will usually have *more* hops than BFS but lower total length."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 5,
   "id": "08-dij",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Dijkstra path hops    : 65\n",
      "Dijkstra cost (µm)    : 312.52\n",
      "Dijkstra visited nodes: 6,097\n",
      "  euclidean sum along path : 2453.36 µm  (should match)\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "sp = shortest_path(STORE, source=source, target=target, weight=\"length\")\n",
    "print(f\"Dijkstra path hops    : {len(sp['path']) - 1}\")\n",
    "print(f\"Dijkstra cost (µm)    : {sp['cost']:.2f}\")\n",
    "print(f\"Dijkstra visited nodes: {sp['visited']:,}\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Cross-check against the explicit euclidean sum along the returned path.\n",
    "euclid = np.linalg.norm(np.diff(P[sp['path']], axis=0), axis=1).sum()\n",
    "print(f\"  euclidean sum along path : {euclid:.2f} µm  (should match)\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "08-md-5",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 5 · A* with a euclidean heuristic\n",
    "\n",
    "Pass a `heuristic(v) → lower bound on remaining distance`. The straight-line distance to the target is admissible (never overestimates) for euclidean edge weights, so A* returns the *same* path as Dijkstra but expands fewer nodes."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 6,
   "id": "08-astar",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "A* path hops          : 44\n",
      "A* cost (µm)          : 554.83\n",
      "A* visited nodes      : 121\n",
      "\n",
      "A*  cost - Dijkstra cost : +242.3051 µm\n",
      "  A* returned a higher cost than Dijkstra. Why: cross-chunk edges\n",
      "  currently fall back to unit weight (length slot missing in core,\n",
      "  tracked as Add 2), so the euclidean heuristic over-estimates the\n",
      "  graph distance through any cross-chunk hop and stops being\n",
      "  admissible. A* therefore can lock onto a suboptimal path before\n",
      "  the true minimum pops.\n",
      "\n",
      "A* / Dijkstra visited ratio: 50.39x\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "target_pos = P[target]\n",
    "def euclid_to_target(v: int) -> float:\n",
    "    return float(np.linalg.norm(P[v] - target_pos))\n",
    "\n",
    "sp_astar = shortest_path(\n",
    "    STORE,\n",
    "    source=source,\n",
    "    target=target,\n",
    "    weight=\"length\",\n",
    "    heuristic=euclid_to_target,\n",
    ")\n",
    "print(f\"A* path hops          : {len(sp_astar['path']) - 1}\")\n",
    "print(f\"A* cost (µm)          : {sp_astar['cost']:.2f}\")\n",
    "print(f\"A* visited nodes      : {sp_astar['visited']:,}\")\n",
    "\n",
    "cost_diff = sp_astar['cost'] - sp['cost']\n",
    "print(f\"\\nA*  cost - Dijkstra cost : {cost_diff:+.4f} µm\")\n",
    "if cost_diff > 1e-6:\n",
    "    print(\n",
    "        \"  A* returned a higher cost than Dijkstra. Why: cross-chunk edges\\n\"\n",
    "        \"  currently fall back to unit weight (length slot missing in core,\\n\"\n",
    "        \"  tracked as Add 2), so the euclidean heuristic over-estimates the\\n\"\n",
    "        \"  graph distance through any cross-chunk hop and stops being\\n\"\n",
    "        \"  admissible. A* therefore can lock onto a suboptimal path before\\n\"\n",
    "        \"  the true minimum pops.\"\n",
    "    )\n",
    "\n",
    "speedup = sp['visited'] / max(sp_astar['visited'], 1)\n",
    "print(f\"\\nA* / Dijkstra visited ratio: {speedup:.2f}x\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "08-md-summary",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Summary\n",
    "\n",
    "| Step | API |\n",
    "|------|-----|\n",
    "| BFS  | `bfs_distances(store, source, max_distance=None)` → `{distances, predecessors}` |\n",
    "| Dijkstra | `shortest_path(store, source, target, weight='length')` → `{path, cost, visited}` |\n",
    "| A* | `shortest_path(store, source, target, weight='length', heuristic=fn)` |\n",
    "\n",
    "Notes\n",
    "\n",
    "- Vertex indices are global (the ordering that `read_graph` returns).\n",
    "- The unweighted call (`weight=None`) is equivalent to BFS but returns a single path instead of the full distance vector.\n",
    "- Cross-chunk edges currently have no per-edge weight slot in core; they fall back to unit weight inside `shortest_path` (tracked alongside core *Add 2*)."
   ]
  }
 ],
